Stimulation of discussions and further correspondence</gtr:impact><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Professional Practitioners</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:year>2014</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput></gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:description>The work revealed a novel membrane channel protein in calcifying coccolithophore phytoplankton that selectively allows protons to be extruded from the cell. This is a newly discovered mechanism for cellular pH regulation in phytoplankton and has implications for understanding the responses of phytoplankton to changing ocean pH.

The finding underpinned the development of a new cellular model for understanding cell surface ionic and pH conditions during photosynthesis and calcification.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Mainly by other academic researchers. The findings will be of value to new generation models of phytoplankton physiology.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>7A5CDFFF-E537-4935-BE19-8588D19D1B22</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Environment</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/A2CE8C56-7503-49AE-B568-DEDF900EE771"><gtr:id>A2CE8C56-7503-49AE-B568-DEDF900EE771</gtr:id><gtr:title>Pan genome of the phytoplankton Emiliania underpins its global distribution.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Nature</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/3843f24dae413069a29f9d34dec57601"><gtr:id>3843f24dae413069a29f9d34dec57601</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Read BA</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2013-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0028-0836</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/5873CF0E-802D-4723-B915-2BF89395AD5C"><gtr:id>5873CF0E-802D-4723-B915-2BF89395AD5C</gtr:id><gtr:title>Changes in pH at the exterior surface of plankton with ocean acidification</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Nature Climate Change</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/e32432d6a392e3c382f69aef0a2fa4a6"><gtr:id>e32432d6a392e3c382f69aef0a2fa4a6</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Flynn K</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2012-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/3DA43648-CA5E-418C-B7EA